          {
            "commit": "19326174e264802b91fb4dfc0c1ea16d8bf3ef7e",
            "subject": "LU-4619 llite: prevent buffer overflow in fiemap"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-06-24 20:39:51.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-04-20 03:38:16.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-3498 kernel: remove uses of IS_ERR_VALUE()",
        "message": "LU-3498 kernel: remove uses of IS_ERR_VALUE()\n\nRemove most uses of IS_ERR_VALUE(). This macro was often given an int\nargument coming from PTR_ERR(). This invokes implementation defined\nbehavior since the long value gotten by applying PTR_ERR() to a kernel\npointer will usually not be representable as an int. Moreover it may\nbe just plain wrong to do this since the expressions IS_ERR(p) and\nIS_ERR_VALUE((int) PTR_ERR(p)) are not equivalent for a general\npointer p.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ib76592a1fc491539d28a51668c7f06347e988f9f\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6759\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
